&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IV Vascular access/ PICC insertion specialist in the Infection Prevention and Control Team&lt;/strong&gt; – Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Andover/Basingstoke/Winchester&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to help develop an expanding nurse led vascular access/ PICC service. You will be part of a small team of nurses working cross site to assess patients for insertion of PICC and Midlines, and difficult cannulation. You will participate in the education of trust staff in the care of vascular access devices and IV therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working patterns will considered for all applicants! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To lead and motivate teams to consistently deliver high quality, safe, compassionate care alongside optimal patient, carer and staff experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To act as patient advocate in line with the NHS long term plan and to actively apply in depth knowledge of holistic/socio-economic and cultural aspects of the care to clients within your specific specialty, acting as a role model and resource for patients, relatives and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be personally competent to lead and train other staff to support the development of clinical competency within the clinical speciality, by conducting clinical assessments as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive multi-disciplinary team that will help develop into the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This job offers the ability to work across sites in a clinical leadership role influencing and collaborating with the multi-professional team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training for your role will be given to enable you to carry out the role IV Vascular Access/PICC specialist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the Trust are happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Infection Prevention &amp; Control Team is made up of clinical specialists in infection control, sepsis, vascular access, Infusion devices and surveillance. We are a very supportive team and work across all sites delivering a high standard of care and support to patients and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vascular access deam&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vision at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to provide outstanding care for every patient. We serve a population of nearly 600,000 people across Hampshire and West Berkshire as well as some people who access our specialist services from across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created in January 2012 the Foundation Trust prioritises the provision of exceptional, compassionate, care delivered by the valued staff working in a culture of collaboration and mutual respect. HHFT employs circa 6,000 people and had a turnover of £382m in 17/18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Four core values (CARE) Compassion, Accountability, Respect and Encourage. These are in place to support of four clear objectives, provide outstanding care of patients, empowering all members of staff, sustainable growth and innovating for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
